Program: Discovery
Title: Natural Born Killers - the sand scorpion
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry6w
Last Broadcast Date: 15 October 2002
Survival of the fittest means that wild animals often have to develop lethal skills. The sand scorpion is only a few centimetres long but is highly adapted to life in the harsh environs of the desert.